    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1361</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 25, 9.35
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Repeated message from <persName corresp="#p_MDB1">Macgowan</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d121fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MDB1">David B. Macgowan</persName>, Consul at Moscow,
                        on detail in Siberia.</note> hitherto undecipherable confirms
                        <persName>Moran</persName>’s<note n="2" xml:id="d121fn2">
                        <persName>Hugh Moran</persName>, representative of the Y.M.C.A. in Siberia;
                        see <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_483">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            p. 483</ref>.</note> report about prisoners at Irkutsk. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SM1">Summers</persName> says Germans advancing from south
                    without resistance. <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">Morris</persName> cables
                        <persName>Emery</persName>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d121fn3">
                        <persName>Henry C. Emery</persName>, in 1917 American member of the
                        Inter-Ally Priority Board at Petrograd (Michelsen commission), was arrested
                        by German forces Mar. 10, 1918, on the Åland Islands when <hi rend="italic"
                            >en route</hi> from Petrograd to Stockholm.</note> taken, sent Berlin.
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCWS1">Crosley</persName>, <persName>Stines</persName>
                    and others at Björneborg.</p>
                <pb facs="0174" n="84" xml:id="pg_84"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName> denies prisoners being armed and
                        <persName corresp="#p_RLCR1">Robins</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d121fn4">
                        <persName corresp="#p_RLCR1">Lieut. Col. Raymond Robins</persName>, in
                        charge of the American Red Cross Commission to Russia.</note> credits denial
                    saying Russian officer and <persName>Webster</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d121fn5">Capt. <persName>William B. Webster</persName>,
                        member of the American Red Cross Commission to Russia.</note> with British
                    officer who <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> Irkutsk to investigate going only to
                    convince me that reports of prisoners organizing are untrue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
